Spending time here reminds you of a conversation from spring, when Brother Aelred was tending a corner of the garden. "This one's a challenge, my son," he said, gesturing at a new basil plant. "It wants warmth and sun we can barely give it here. But there's a brother of ours---he came from sunnier lands, seeking refuge. He never complains, but I see the homesickness in his eyes." Aelred touched the leaves gently. "If I can coax this to grow, it will remind him of home. A small kindness, perhaps, but sometimes those matter most." You will miss Aelred so much.

> TASTE IT
You try a single leaf: it's sharp at first, then peppery and a bit like liquorice.

> EAT IT
