[The score has just gone up by 2 points.]

> LOOK UP HEMLOCK IN HERBAL
Hemlock: a deadly poison, to be kept only for its limited medicinal uses in treating spasm and pain. Death comes slowly, as a creeping paralysis from the feet upward, while the mind remains clear until the end. Socrates himself is said to have died thus. The smell of the crushed leaves is foul, like mice.

